      <solution id="idm334480">
        <title>40, 41 &amp; 42. Osteogenesis imperfecta</title>
        <para id="id2254380">An autosomal dominant disorder marked by defective 
formation of collagen. Its cardinal manifestations are blue sclerae, fragile 
bones, and deafness. The blue discoloration occurs when thinning of the sclera 
allows the underlying choroid to become visible.</para>
        <para id="id2254394">Although blue sclerae occur chiefly in osteogenesis 
imperfecta, they also appear occasionally in pseudoxanthoma elasticum, Ehlers-
Danlos syndrome, and Marfanâ€™s disease. Rarely, they are seen in patients with 
iron deficiency, rheumatoid arthritis, or myasthenia gravis. </para>
      </solution>
